race.comment: PRINCESS SAKIKO (14) has been runner-up last two runs, the latest this course and distance when finding the line strongly and going down narrowly. Has drawn for a soft run Overdue for a win and looks a top chance again. WATT ON EARTH (12) dropped back to 1400m and although ran fifth was only a length away. Has run very well both starts at the mile and gets back there now. Worth following up. PETE THE PROPHET (4) improved sharply at second outing when getting over an extra furlong and gets even more ground this time. Has upside and expected to run well. PRIDE OF PARIAH (5) was terrible fresh but is far better than that. Best figures stack up.
